\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Reward functions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our project uses two reward functions as heuristics to guide the meal planning
 process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
MinimizeWasteProblem Function: This function scores meals based on how soon
 their ingredients will expire.
 It sum over all ingredients in a meal (action):
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathrm{score}=\sum\frac{1}{\mathrm{expirationdate}-\mathrm{currentdate}+1}
\]

\end_inset

for each ingredient.
 This heuristic pushes the solvers to use ingredients that would spoil soon,
 directly addressing our goal of reducing food waste.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
ParametersProblem Function: This function builds on the waste minimization
 score and adds considerations for other meal attributes.
 It normalizes various parameters (like taste rating or preparation time)
 to a 
